Hotel Management Database

Project Overview:-

This project demonstrates the design and implementation of a Hotel Management Database using SQL.
It includes table creation, relationships, and sample data to simulate real-world hotel booking and billing operations.

Database Structure:-
1️.Users Table

Stores customer details:
User ID
Name
Phone Number
Email
Billing Address

2️.Bookings Table

Tracks room bookings:
Booking ID
Booking Date
Room Number
User ID (Foreign Key)

3️.Items Table

Contains food/menu items:
Item ID
Item Name
Item Price

4️.Booking Commercials Table

Stores billing details:
Bill ID
Booking ID
Item Ordered
Quantity
Bill Date

5. Relationships
One user → Many bookings
One booking → Multiple items
Items linked through billing table

6.Concepts Used
SQL DDL (CREATE TABLE)
SQL DML (INSERT INTO)
Primary Keys
Foreign Keys
Relational Database Design

7.Sample Data

The database includes:
5 users
6 bookings
8 menu items
Multiple billing transactions

8.How to Use
Open MySQL / PostgreSQL / any SQL tool
Run the SQL script file
Tables and data will be created automatically
Perform queries for analysis

9.Learning Outcomes
Understanding database schema design
Working with relationships (FK constraints)
Writing structured SQL queries
Real-world data modeling
